A balanced framework can safeguard early, time‑sensitive decision-making and privacy, set later‑pregnancy protections tied to medical viability and serious health risk, and include clear, workable exceptions for rape, incest, severe fetal anomalies, and threats to the pregnant person’s life or major bodily functions. Lasting common ground also means investing in upstream supports—contraception, accurate education, maternal healthcare, and economic and parenting resources—so fewer pregnancies become crises and fewer families feel forced into any option.
